derivation.yuyuan_name: early 17th cent.: from Latin honorarius, from honor 'honour'

entry.tran: （称号、成员资格）荣誉的，名誉的
entry.def: An honorary title or membership of a group is given to someone without their needing to have the necessary qualifications, usually because of their public achievements.

example.ex: He will be awarded the honorary degree in a ceremony at Newcastle University.

entry.def: Honorary is used to describe an official job that is done without payment.
